Numbers indicate the growing pervasiveness of online communications and friendships.

“The average adult in Belarus has about six intimate friendships, two of whom they see frequently, and at least eight superficial ones, who they speak to or socialize with occasionally. Facebook is the source of about 20 percent of those friendships, and takes about half the place of in-person relationships in Belarus. On average, a typical Belarusian citizen has 115 Facebook friends, and 3 percent of those Facebook friends are genuinely intimate, the Bis- study found. About 20 percent of those internet friends exist only online.”

Surprisingly the article claims Belarus “has higher fertility rates would most developed countries. . . ”

“Belarus leads all other countries in fertility, second only to the African country of Niger, which has very low living standards and a high mortality rate. Belarus averages, 0.4 births per women of child-bearing age, whereas the average N America has about 1.7, and highest US rates, Utah, Texas, Louisiana have up to 2.4.Two common, but novel, practices in the Belarus marriage culture are that the bride must be a virgin when she marries, and that multiple wives are often common especially for wealthy men.”
